×008Starting Up
===========×
When starting the mag, the screenmode is switching to
640x512  and  some kind of futuristic stylish picture
made  by  ×031Dan  Dee×  fades  in.  This guy also did the
second  titlepicture  showing  a photo of a face. The
pictures  are not bad, but I've seen better and those
are  more  looking  a bit raytraced, less pixeled. In
addition it says 'jp#13 2003' in the corner. A little
slip  I  guess.  In the end, I know how hard it is to
get titlepictures from people nowadays, so its better
with  some  kind of titlepicture than nothing at all.

After  waiting  forever or simply by clicking the LMB
we  are  suddenly inside the heart of the Dinosaur. A
collection  with  the impressive size of 84 articles.
not   bad.

×008The Surface
===========×
Something  about  the  inside graphics then. To reuse
cliparts  doesn't  matter to me, but when they appear
in  different  magazines  I think its a bit loosy. In
this  case,  the first clipart to appear when opening
the  mag  is  made  by  ×031Bridgeclaw×  (I guess) and was
already   used   in   Devotion   #2.

I like the panelgraphics by ×031Da Freak/RNO×. In contrast
to my own panels in Cows n Snakefights 5, those are a
bit  easier to understand. One thing I dont like with
them  though, is when clicking the mouse, for example
on  'Next' the graphics is replaced by an arrow. More
nice  would  be  keeping  the  same  concept  on  the
buttons.

The modules from Jurassic Pack are reviewed seperatly
in another article.   But six modules are impressive!

×008User   actions
==============×
When  we are into the interaction I have to critisize
that  mouse  action. It's simply terrible. When going
to next/previous article, the user can choose between
clicking  up and down, but he can also move the mouse
to  the buttom of the screen. ×031Stingray/Scarab× told me
that  this  function  could be turned off, but I have
nothing against that this functions does not exist at
all! When the user moves the mouse left or right over
the  panelgraphics,  he may by mistake go to the next
article.  Quite  annoying. After I used the multitask
function  (all  new  code  by Stingray btw) and going
into  an  article,  it seems to crash and I cant move
between  the sections. And the articles are messed up
×008(testing  on  A1200, 68040/FPU, 8mb fast)×. So have to
restart   it.
