The  quality  differs. I noticed that ×031Gone's× articles
are quite short this time. In general only 1-2 pages,
also more personal feelings and poetry from his side.
But  in  the  end,  it's  flowers  (eastereggs?)  for
everyone   inside   JP13.

Of  course  there  are some of the usual quite boring
articles  to  be found here as just in every diskmag.
The  themes for the common topics are like: 'swapping
is  dead',  'scene  is  dead', 'all was better before
when there were less 3d' etc. blah blah. Well writers
just  don't  stop  to  write  about   those   topics.

×008A huge job is made in the demo spotting 2003 and 2004
articles,×  where  the  editorers  browse  through the
happenings in Amiga releases. Great job and much more
intresting  to  read than going through 1000 comments
on  Pouet.net.  A  short  note  on these demospotting
articles:  I  think  that  the  critizism  concerning
Jamaica  ROM demos were quite unfair. You should have
in mind that those are more or less ×031partyhacks×. There
is  NO  chance  to  hold  a  party  2  weeks   before
Mekka&Symposium  (aka  Breakpoint)  and  expect  full
quality.

Some  support  were  from  new writers, and some old.
Overall  I  didnt  got the feeling that only the same
people  writes  in  discmags  when  reading  JP   13.

The disaster article, was the Breakpoint 2004 report.
Within  30 seconds, you realize that this guy doesn't
have  a clue about the Amiga scene. Instead he gladly
mention  other  names,  like  ×031Scamp×, the mainorgaz of
Breakpoint  and  I  get  this  'common,  give  me   a
