×008A  14th Pack?
=============×
To  answer this question, we need to know who will go
on with the developing of the diskmag. Ghandy and his
kicking  team can easily fix articles they had proved
to  us.  I  heard  some  time ago that JP æ04æ
should be a production for ×031moods plateau×
pur. If this is still the  plans, I'm
quite skeptic. The engine is since 
JP 13 100% made by ×031Scarab×. Earlier, 
pieces were taken from mr.Tickle of
Darkage  (nowadays called Xeron btw).

My thoughts are that even if Ghandy 
wants to release JP just under  the 
house of moods plateau, this will 
not  be that easy. Who will code a 
new engine? It's a matter of time 
and also questions like if there are
enough  skills in moods plateau for 
an editor Engine? And even if Ghandy 
still is a doublemember of Scarab,
and probably can take the enginebag 
with him home to Duesseldorf, I think it's a question
of moral  when stealing  the hard work from  ×031Stingray×
or ×031Scicco's× soundmachine for Digibooster  modules. 
I hope for a new issue, even if I never thought  that
was possible in my article in latest issue.  The  JP-
staff seems pretty sure they will make the 14:th pack
already this sommer.  No way!  I think it will arrive
earliest this autumn.  And hopefully  a work  between
Scarab^moods.  The  both  groups  are   complementing
eachother.  And  instead of twinbrothers between Zito
and   Ghandy,   I   want   to   see   twin-groups.


×008a Last tip
==========×
Since I have done some cliparts myself for JP, I know
the  freedom  the  artists has. He can choose his own
palette  and some different sizes are allowed. But in
the end I think its better if you use a fixed palette
instead.  Then  you  have the possibility to use more
than  one  clipart  for  every article (I assume that
Stringray  loads  one  palette for every article, and
not for every page). Then the colors 1,2,17,18 and 19
for  colorizing  texts  don't  have  to  be   treated
seperatly   anymore   as   it   is   now.

